intro: Acronychia cuspidata, commonly known as the narrow-leaved acronychia, is a species of flowering plant in the family Burseraceae. It is native to eastern Australia, particularly found in the coastal regions of New South Wales and Queensland. The plant is a small to medium-sized evergreen tree that can grow up to 10 meters in height. Its leaves are narrow and leathery, with a dark green upper surface and a lighter underside. The flowers are small and yellow, appearing in clusters, and the tree produces woody fruits that contain small, edible seeds.
